,"body":"In pgcli, click crashes when I set PAGER to be empty.\n\n``` python\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/home/jonathan/env/pt/bin/pgcli\", line 9, in <module>\n    load_entry_point('pgcli==0.19.0', 'console_scripts', 'pgcli')()\n  ...\n  File \"/home/jonathan/git/pgcli/pgcli/main.py\", line 353, in run_cli\n    click.echo_via_pager('\\n'.join(output))\n  File \"/home/jonathan/env/pt/lib/python3.4/site-packages/click-4.1-py3.4.egg/click/termui.py\", line 203, in echo_via_pager\n    return pager(text + '\\n', color)\n  File \"/home/jonathan/env/pt/lib/python3.4/site-packages/click-4.1-py3.4.egg/click/_termui_impl.py\", line 263, in pager\n    return _pipepager(text, os.environ['PAGER'], color)\n  File \"/home/jonathan/env/pt/lib/python3.4/site-packages/click-4.1-py3.4.egg/click/_termui_impl.py\", line 292, in _pipepager\n    if color is None and cmd_detail[0] == 'less':\nIndexError: list index out of range\n```\n\n`PipePager` is called with an empty `os.environ['PAGER']`: https://github.com/mitsuhiko/click/blob/dbd40696e31409a50eb4722c806b4ac1c527ca8c/click/_termui_impl.py#L263\n\nSo, splitting an empty string makes `cmd_detail` an empty list. `[0]` gives that `IndexError`:\nhttps://github.com/mitsuhiko/click/blob/dbd40696e31409a50eb4722c806b4ac1c527ca8c/click/_termui_impl.py#L292\n","closed_by":{"login":"untitaker","id":837573,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjgzNzU3Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/837573?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker","html_url":"https://github.com/untitaker","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker